 10→ *
 11→ * 1. INITIALIZATION (0-5%)
 12→ *    - Validate mathematical functions
 13→ *    - Set up progress tracking
 14→ *
 15→ * 2. PREPROCESSING (5-25%)
 16→ *    - Adaptive thresholding → binary text
 17→ *    - Canny edge detection → edge map
 18→ *    - Morphological operations → connected components
 19→ *    - Hough line detection → initial text line estimates
 20→ *    - Contour detection → page boundary
 21→ *
 22→ * 3. SPAN DETECTION (25-40%)
 23→ *    - Compute edge density map (smoothed edge information)
 24→ *    - Extract initial span estimates from Hough lines
 25→ *    - Refine spans using gradient descent (50 iterations)
 26→ *    - Each span has position + curvature parameters
 27→ *
 28→ * 4. MODEL FITTING (40-70%)
 29→ *    - Sample keypoints along refined spans
 30→ *    - Fit 16-parameter cubic sheet model
 31→ *    - Use Levenberg-Marquardt optimization (up to 100 iterations)
 32→ *    - Minimize reprojection error of keypoints
 33→ *
 34→ * 5. REMAPPING (70-95%)
 35→ *    - Generate transformation maps (mapX, mapY)
 36→ *    - For each output pixel, compute source location in input
 37→ *    - Apply remap with cubic interpolation
 38→ *    - Optional: adaptive threshold for clean text output
 39→ *
 40→ * 6. FINALIZATION (95-100%)
 41→ *    - Generate debug visualizations (if enabled)
 42→ *    - Collect processing metrics
 43→ *    - Return dewarped image
 44→ *
 45→ * Error handling:
 46→ * - If any phase fails, return original image (graceful degradation)
 47→ * - Log errors for debugging
 48→ * - Populate debug data with partial results
 49→ *
 50→ * Progress reporting:
 51→ * - Each phase reports progress 0-100 with descriptive messages
 52→ * - Allows UI to show real-time feedback to user
 53→ */
